# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Digital Portfolio — environment variables
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values you want.
# Anything left commented falls back to mock mode for that showcase.
#
# Quick reference — what each key gates:
#
#   ┌─────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────┐
#   │ Variable                    │ Used by                                   │
#   ├─────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────┤
#   │ ANTHROPIC_API_KEY           │ Showcases 1, 2, 3, 4 (all generation)     │
#   │ OPENAI_API_KEY              │ Showcase 1 embeddings                     │
#   │ DATABASE_URL                │ Showcase 1 pgvector retrieval             │
#   │ TAVILY_API_KEY              │ Showcase 2 web search                     │
#   │ OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY      │ Showcase 4 live weather tool              │
#   │ BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN       │ Showcase 2 PDF storage (production only)  │
#   │ UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL      │ rate-limit middleware (production)        │
#   │ UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN    │ rate-limit middleware (production)        │
#   │ PGSSL_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED   │ optional Postgres TLS opt-out             │
#   │ GITHUB_TOKEN                │ optional GitHub activity context          │
#   └─────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
# Minimum to demo all 4 showcases locally: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.
# Full real mode: everything except PGSSL_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED and GITHUB_TOKEN.
#
# See docs/DEPLOYMENT.md for the Vercel / Neon / Blob provisioning steps.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REQUIRED — Anthropic Claude (generation)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Powers the chat / research / crew / playground LLM calls. Without
# this key, every showcase falls back to canned heuristic output.
# Get from https://console.anthropic.com/
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REAL MODE — OpenAI embeddings (Showcase 1)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used to embed both the corpus (one-off, via `npm run seed`) and
# the user query (per request, in /api/chat). Without this key,
# Showcase 1 retrieval falls back to keyword overlap.
# Get from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Cost: ~$0.02 per 1M tokens (negligible for this corpus).
#
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REAL MODE — Neon Postgres with pgvector (Showcase 1)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Stores the embedded corpus_chunks table for cosine-similarity
# retrieval. Use the *pooled* (pgBouncer) connection string for
# serverless. The seed script runs `CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS
# vector` for you.
# Get from https://console.neon.tech > Project > Connection > Pooled.
#
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:hash@ep-xxxxxx-pooler.neon.tech/portfolio?sslmode=require
#
# Postgres TLS validation defaults to ON (rejectUnauthorized: true).
# Neon's certs are signed by public CAs and validate against Node's
# root store. Only set this to "false" for a self-signed cluster.
#
# PGSSL_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=false


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REAL MODE — Tavily web search (Showcase 2)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Research Agent runs 3 web searches per report. Without this
# key, searchNode falls back to clearly-labelled offline source
# stubs.
# Free tier at https://tavily.com — 1000 searches/month.
# Cost: ~$0.008 per basic search.
#
# TAVILY_API_KEY=tvly-...


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REAL MODE — OpenWeather (Showcase 4)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by the playground get_weather tool. Without this key, weather
# falls back to canned London mock data.
# Free tier at https://openweathermap.org/api — "Current Weather Data".
#
# OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY=...


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PRODUCTION — Vercel Blob (Showcase 2 PDF storage)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required on Vercel. The SSE invocation that runs the research
# pipeline and the GET /api/research-pdf invocation are different
# serverless functions — reports must live in shared storage so
# the download survives the handoff. Without this token,
# research-store falls back to an in-memory Map (works only in
# `npm run dev`).
#
# Auto-injected when you create + link the Blob store from the
# Vercel dashboard. The canonical URL is discovered via the
# @vercel/blob head() SDK call, so no separate hostname is needed.
#
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=vercel_blob_rw_...


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PRODUCTION — Upstash Redis (rate-limit middleware)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backs the per-IP sliding-window rate limiter in src/middleware.ts.
# Without these vars, the middleware logs a warning and passes
# every request through (fail-open) — fine for `npm run dev`,
# NOT fine for production.
#
# Free tier at https://console.upstash.com — 10,000 commands/day
# (≈ 2,500 rate-limited requests/day before paying).
#
# Tier limits (sized to per-call costs in src/lib/agent/llm-caps.ts):
#   /api/research-stream     3 / hour  per IP  (most expensive: ~$0.057/call)
#   /api/crew-stream         5 / hour  per IP  (~$0.068/call)
#   /api/chat               10 / 10m  per IP  (~$0.014/call)
#   /api/playground-stream  10 / 10m  per IP  (~$0.018/call)
#   /api/* (global burst)   30 / minute per IP  (catches scrapers)
#
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://xxxx-xxxx.upstash.io
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=...


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL — GitHub API (higher rate limits, seeding live activity)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Reserved for future GitHub activity integration. Not currently
# read by any code path; documented here so the variable surface
# is complete.
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...
